    <prp:code/>
    <prp:abstract>We propose high-resolution ALMA/ACA Band 3 Sunyaev-Zel'dovich observations of the prominent shock front in the 'Bullet' cluster of galaxies. Current X-ray instruments lack the combination of wide effective area above 10keV, sufficient photon number counts and high angular resolution (&lt;10'') to derive the associated pressure signature along the shock arc in detail. The strength of the discontinuity in the SZ map will allow us to deduce a pressure-based shock Mach number estimate and, in conjunction with a given geometry and de-projected density model, the mean post-shock electron temperature, whose value will give vital insight into the electron heating mechanisms during such merger events. ALMA/ACA SZ observations will not only indicate the projected pressure discontinuity across the shock front but will also allow for the projected bow shock pressure geometry to be mapped for the very first time in SZ. 
</prp:abstract>
